Taiwan Stocks: Chunghwa Picture Tubes, Quanta Computer, UMC

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-12-09T06:19:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-09/taiwan-stocks-chunghwa-picture-tubes-quanta-computer-umc.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual (TWSE)  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are at the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index fell 1.3 percent to 6,893.30, the lowest
close since Nov. 25. The benchmark gauge retreated 3.5 percent
this week.  Chunghwa Picture Tubes Ltd. (2474)  (2475 TT) sank by the 6.9
percent daily limit to NT$1.09. The flat panel maker was fined
297 million won ($261,000) for alleged price fixing by the Korea
Fair Trade Commission, the company said in an exchange statement
yesterday. Chunghwa Picture’s November sales fell 20 percent to
NT$4 billion ($132 million) from a year earlier, according to a
separate statement filed with the bourse.  Quanta Computer Inc. (2382)  (2382 TT) lost 2.9 percent to
NT$59.90, the biggest drop since Nov. 24. The world’s largest
maker of laptops said November sales fell 3 percent to NT$96.5
billion from a year earlier, according to a statement to the
 Taiwan Stock Exchange .  United Microelectronics Corp. (2303)  (2303 TT) retreated 2.7
percent to NT$12.45, the biggest loss since Nov. 23. The world’s
second-largest custom maker of chips said November sales fell 23
percent to NT$8 billion from a year earlier, according to a
statement filed to the Taiwan Stock Exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
